cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the task of video reconstruction from a single blurred image, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a novel video autoencoder network that performs unsupervised learning for motion representation, which involves the use of deep learning techniques such as convolutional filters and recurrent design. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and graphics (cs.GR).
